Run in NetBeans
Step 1:

File → New Project
Java with Ant → Web Application

Step 2:

Choose Tomcat server.

Step 3:

Right-click Source Packages → New → Servlet

Name: HelloServlet

Step 4:

Modify doGet method:

response.getWriter().println("<h1>Hello World</h1>");

Step 5:

Right-click Project → Run

Browser opens automatically.

Alternative (Without Annotation):

If annotation doesn't work, use web.xml

web.xml
<web-app>
    <servlet>
        <servlet-name>HelloServlet</servlet-name>
        <servlet-class>HelloServlet</servlet-class>
    </servlet>

    <servlet-mapping>
        <servlet-name>HelloServlet</servlet-name>
        <url-pattern>/hello</url-pattern>
    </servlet-mapping>
</web-app>

Expected Output:

Hello World from Servlet!
